==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Substruction
<hw>Sub*struc"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>substructio</ets>, fr. <ets>substruere</ets>,
<ets>substructum</ets>, to build beneath; <ets>sub</ets> under +
<ets>struere</ets> to build.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>Underbuilding; the foundation, or any preliminary structure
intended to raise the lower floor or basement of a building above the
natural level of the ground.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is a magnificent strong building, with a
<qex>substruction</qex> very remarkable.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Substructure</ent>⟦br⟧
